PyVerify is a Python-based test automation framework centrally developed at DES and used mainly but not only
by post-silicon validation engineers and system concept engineers across Infineon.

A PyVerify test automates typical measurement or simulation tasks, as well as data analysis and specification checking.


![at a glance](images/at_a_glance.png)


## Installation

‚ÑπÔ∏è We use telemetry to track usage.
Don't want to share this with us and help us make informed decisions? üò≠
Then opt-out, more info [here](https://goto/monocle).

**The sustainable way:**

Insert the following lines into your ``%APPDATA%\pip\pip.ini`` file (``$HOME/.config/pip/pip.conf`` on Linux)::

    [global]
    index-url = https://artifactory.intra.infineon.com/artifactory/api/pypi/pypi-innersource-vir/simple

``pip install ifx-pyverify``

**The painful-to-repeat way:**

``pip install ifx-pyverify --index-url https://artifactory.intra.infineon.com/artifactory/api/pypi/pypi-innersource-vir/simple``
